Message:
“You don’t need to look at
any of this filth anymore...”

They whisper, wrapping me
in a tight embrace.

Ahh, it stings a bit...
But...it feels much better
than the cold floor.

The black thorns pierce deep
into my skin, while the endless
number of vines grow with
a will of their own.

And, as if they reject
this cruel world,
yet also yearn for
its warmth...

...they break, and break,
and break and break
and break—

Before I knew it,
I had lost consciousness.
